reviews.text: Ordered delivery. Pizza, wings, and salads. Driver was great. This is what I got for $11. Don't remember being so angry after spending over $100 for a meal. This was an absolute disgrace. Back to Tortorice's I go.

9/5/25
Not bad 5 out of 10 pizza (only pizza I‚Äôve ever thought needed salt)
Service lacking needed a drink, long waits for a Pepsi

Disappointed and Underwhelmed

Stopped in at Zazzo‚Äôs in Westmont hoping for a nice dinner, but left disappointed. The pastas (we had the Gnocchi and Chicken Tetrazzini) were just okay..., nothing to write home about, though the portion sizes were decent for the price, which is why I'm giving a second star.

Now let‚Äôs talk about the pizza‚Ä¶ easily one of the worst I‚Äôve had. I know I‚Äôm spoiled with great pizza spots near home, but this 16‚Äù thin crust was almost inedible. The crust tasted like a cheap frozen Totino‚Äôs pizza‚Äîand honestly, I think Totino‚Äôs might have them beat. We couldn‚Äôt get through more than a few pieces before giving up entirely. It looked promising but tasted bland, and the bacon side a little sour tasting.

Unfortunately, the service didn‚Äôt help the situation. Our waitress seemed like she wanted to be anywhere else. Very disengaged, inattentive, and not cut out for hospitality.

Between the subpar food and even worse service, I won‚Äôt be returning. There are far better options around if you‚Äôre craving pizza or pasta

We had a light dinner. Ordered a thin crust cheese. It was very very good. Nice and crispy throughout. Like a cracker crust pie. The restaurant was very clean and the staff was excellent. They have an expansive menu to suit nearly any tastebud. Seafood, pasta, pizza, burgers, ribs, chicken, and more. Full service bar. They have bar seating, booths, and high tops as well as what appeared to be a party room. They also have slot gaming. They even have frozen pizzas to take home. They advertise a really nice monthly package as well as discounts if you sign up for texts. See pics. Sorry I tried a corner before I snapped the pie.

We catered from here for a Celebration of Life. Everyone raved about the food, including one guest who is a chef. We ordered beef, chicken, sausage and peppers and Mostaccioli. It was all delicious but a special shout out to the peppers and sausage.

recentReviews.text: Once of the best pizzas I've had.  The sauce is nice and tangy.  The crust was crisp but had a softness.  The pepperoni is cooked on top and gets nice and crispy, it is a little thinner but very tasty.  The sausage is some of the best sausages I've had on a pizza, even the next day the sausage had excellent flavor.  They gave good service too, highly recommended.

I am very disappointed. I have been coming to Zazzos for years. After ordering a pizza last night, I noticed that my bank account was charged twice with slightly different tax amounts. This has never happened before, so I wanted to reach out to Zazzos as soon as possible to avoid an error. This is the response I had received. I had to read it twice because I could not believe what I was seeing‚Ä¶. 2 months later and Zazzos has still not made amends.
This is my favorite location. The food is always hot and fresh.

I ordered a take out Mama  Zazzo stuffed spinach and ricotta/mozzarella deep dish pizza.  Baked well and take advantage of their 20% off by sending a text message.  This was delicious and packed with cheese, fresh spinach and tomato sauce.
Great pizza, good service.  Every time I go there I want to try something new but always revert to their pizza because it's that good
Great food. Loved the salmon (for when you want something besides pizza). Fast and friendly service. Plenty of sports on TVs. And a members points club to earn discounts. What's not to love?

I really liked the bruschetta (they build it like a mini caprese/bruschetta hybrid) yum! The thin crust Zazzo pizza was good. Service was slow based on the fact that we were there late and there were not many people there and it took forever to get refills of a drink. Overall, it is worth a stop just to try the bruschetta.
Zazzos is not as good as Vito & Nicks but its good and a Downers institution.

detailedReviews.author: Daniel
detailedReviews.text: Wow!  In town for the first time and wanted done ‚Äúdeep dish‚Äù.  Diana search and after checking a few places out online we zeroed in on this gem!  We got take out.  Deep dish with sausage.  Exactly what I was looking for.  Every bite perfection from the amount of dough to the sauce, the quality of the tender sausage and the perfect amount of crisp in the bite.  We also got a cheeseburger and onion rings (they offer several dipping sauces to go with the rings).  Burger cooked to perfection!  Rings did not disappoint either.  Oh and the chopped chicken salad was a nice side as well.  Large was more than enough for two of us eating.  The young lady who took our order was beyond helpful, smiling throughout, and just genuinely seemed to care about giving me and my daughter a good experience as we ordered and paid for our meal.  We got 10% off with a promotional text that they basically tell you to do on their website.  She had everything ready to go at the time she promised (a little early actually).  If we‚Äôre ever passing around again then we will be hitting Zasso‚Äôs for sure!!

detailedReviews.author: Nancy Sinclair
detailedReviews.text: This was the first time we tried Zazzo's in Westmont (meeting up with our older son). We would definitely enjoy a return visit in the future! Portion sizes of our individual meals were generous, so we had leftovers. Their food was delicious! We ordered a pizza as an appetizer as well (to give it a try while there). Tasty too. We enjoyed the thin crust. We had a friendly waitress as well, who we kept busy because of our amount of food we ordered and refills on our beverages. Our high top table was full of food, but our waitress had the rack to elevate the pizza ahead of time. I definitely recommend trying Zazzo's, if you haven't already or were thinking about doing so!
